// A recursive `#[inline]` fn would splice forever (each splice re-enters the
// body, which calls the fn again). `inline_check` rejects it up front with a
// clean diagnostic rather than letting the backend splice hit its depth guard
// (planning/inline_bodies.md "Nested/recursive inline").
#[inline]
fn loop_forever(a: uint(8)) -> uint(8) {
    loop_forever(a)
}
